Recurrent urinary tract infections (UTIs) can be caused by various factors, including poor hygiene, sexual activity, and certain medical conditions. To prevent UTIs, it's important to maintain good personal hygiene, drink plenty of water, and avoid憋尿 (holding urine in your bladder).
